data_table.description: 8-EPI-Isoprostane in Urine, Offspring Exam 8 and Omni 1 Exam 3

variable.name: shareid
variable.description: Framingham Heart Study participant SHARe ID number

variable.name: cvper
variable.description: Coefficient of variation for those done in duplicate

variable.name: res1
variable.comment: If RES1 was less than or equal to the lowest detectable limit of 2.7 pg/mL, then RES1 was set to 2.7 pg/mL (there were no observations below the detectable limit for RES1).

variable.name: res2
variable.comment: If RES2 was less than or equal to the lowest detectable limit of 2.7 pg/mL, then RES2 was set to 2.7 pg/mL (there were no observations below the detectable limit for RES2).

variable.name: iso
variable.comment: This is the average Isoprostane value of RES1 and RES2. If ISO was less than or equal to the lowest detectable limit of 2.7 pg/mL, then ISO was set to 2.7 pg/mL (there were no observations below the detectable limit for ISO). 10.0 - 5048.95 FOR FLAG = 2; 10.0 - 3184.55 FOR FLAG = 3; 10.0 - 220.54 FOR FLAG = 4

variable.name: flag
variable.comment: When doing analysis, use the variable ISO where FLAG = 2. Phantoms have their FHS ID number listed under IDTYPE and ID, with their phantom id number listed under PHANTOM_ID. When looking at phantom samples, use FLAG = 3 records as well as their corresponding FHS ID number in FLAG = 2.
variable.value: FHS samples that can be used for analysis, done in duplicate
